cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.OH, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper deals with exploiting symmetries in optimal control problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). The method presented in the paper is also relevant to optimization (cs.OH) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it provides a way to reduce the dimensionality of dynamic programming iterations, which is a common problem in these fields. Finally, the paper uses a general framework that can be applied to a wide range of application problems, which is a characteristic of machine learning (cs.LG).
